 "display": {
  "title": {
   "translate": "Enchantment Theory"
  },
  "subtitle": {
   "text": "Immersive Enchanting replaces randomness with cost. Pay the price. Get what you want."
  },
  "description": [
   "◆━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━◆",
   "  CH.03 · ENCHANTMENT THEORY",
   "◆━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━◆",
   "",
   "▸ Immersive Enchanting replaces vanilla's RNG system.",
   "  You choose the enchantment.",
   "  You pay the material cost.",
   "  You get exactly what you paid for.",
   "",
   "◈ IMMERSIVE ENCHANTING MECHANICS",
   "  └ Enchanting Table: still the core block",
   "  └ Chiseled Bookshelves: enhances the table power",
   "    place books in them to increase max enchantment level",
   "  └ Ancient Books: contain specific enchantments",
   "    found in dungeons, strongholds, buried treasure",
   "    apply directly to gear — no RNG",
   "  └ Material Cost: XP + specific materials per enchant",
   "    better enchants cost more XP and rarer materials",
   "  └ No random rolls: you see all available enchants",
   "    and their costs before committing",
   "",
   "◈ EARLY ENCHANT PRIORITY",
   "  └ 1. Mending — essential if you have an XP farm",
   "  └ 2. Unbreaking III — reduces durability loss",
   "  └ 3. Efficiency IV+ — speeds up mining",
   "  └ 4. Protection III+ — reduces armor damage",
   "  └ 5. Sharpness/Power — combat output",
   "",
   "◈ SCROLL: Enchantment Theory",
   "  └ Found in: library chests, enchanter's workshop,",
   "    scholar ruins, dungeon bookshelves",
   "  └ Research time: 20 min",
   "  └ Unlocks: full Immersive Enchanting system,",
   "    Ancient Books source awareness",
   "",
   "▸ The old world had enchanters who knew the price",
   "  of every word of power.",
   "  This scroll is their catalog.",
   "",
   "▶ Find The Enchantment Theory scroll [check]",
   "▶ Craft 4 Chiseled Bookshelves",
   "▶ Craft an Enchanting Table",
   "",
   "◇ Ch08 Deep Dark and Ch09 Eye Hunt drop Ancient Books",
   "  in abundance. Enchanting gets much stronger",
   "  once you have consistent dungeon access."
  ],
